Key Match Events: England led early but was left hanging on for a 1-1 draw at the Waldstadion in Frankfurt.
Denmark played better despite the draw.
Pre-Game Insights: Prince William posted a pre-game message on his official account on X saying 'May the best team win.'
Post-Match Reflections: Both teams are in contention to advance to the knockout round at Euro 2024 in Germany.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The king of Denmark and the future king of England shook hands on a draw between their national teams.
Prince William is president of the English Football Association and a regular spectator at games played by the team, known as the Three Lions.
King Felipe VI of Spain was at the later game Thursday where Spain was playing Italy in Gelsenkirchen.
